session-appended 2026-05-20 expl-demo follow-up #2 (re-validation correction + new AI-blinding finding). Anchors re-checked against current HEAD with uncommitted spec_id plumbing (router.rs +1 line at :1569; events_ws now :1695; auth_layer :100-120; constant_eq :155-164; check_query_token :142-153; delete_project_repo :906; test_repo_connectivity :976; read_local_git_remote :1088 — pre-existing findings still pin).

CORRECTION to finding #6 (SSRF via AI base_url): re-tracing the config → adapter flow shows `cfg.ai.api_base` has NO consumer in the workspace. AnthropicSdkAdapter is constructed at ai_pipeline.rs:211, :523, :825, :1219 — all four sites call `AnthropicSdkAdapter::new(api_key, tracker)` and never `.with_base_url(cfg.ai.api_base)`. The adapter retains DEFAULT_BASE_URL = "https://api.anthropic.com" (anthropic.rs:32, :123). Additionally every pass (payload synthesis, spec derivation, chain reasoning, exploration) early-returns when `!matches!(config.runtime, ConfigAiRuntime::Anthropic)` (ai_pipeline.rs:193, :505, :796, etc.). Net: the local-llm runtime accepts configuration but ships no client. The SSRF described in finding #6 does not fire — `local_llm_url` is written to TOML and otherwise inert. Finding #6 should be downgraded to a *configuration-acceptance-with-no-implementation* defect; the IMDS payload hint is not exploitable.

